[Modified from the android-rpi original to use the automotive specific config]

# Download Android source with local_manifests
 Refer to http://source.android.com/source/downloading.html

 $ repo init -u https://android.googlesource.com/platform/manifest -b android-12.1.0_r21
 $ git clone https://github.com/snappautomotive/firmware_rpi-local_manifests .repo/local_manifests -b sa-arpi-12L
 $ repo sync

# Build for Raspberry Pi 4
 https://github.com/snappautomotive/firmware-device_snappautomotive_rpi/tree/sa-arpi-12L

Use -j[n] option on sync & build steps, if build host has a good number of CPU cores.
